genresAdvancedInfo.name: german street punk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: German street punk is a subgenre of punk rock that originated in Germany in the late 1970s. It is characterized by its raw, aggressive sound and socially conscious lyrics that often address issues such as politics, poverty, and inequality. German street punk bands often incorporate elements of oi!, ska, and hardcore punk into their music.
